@@ -0,0 +1,54 @@
+# RunPod TRON GPU Pattern Search Smoke
+
+## Purpose
+
+This is the first TRON GPU search smoke for the VanitySearch adaptation.
+
+It verifies that the existing VanitySearch GPU point-walking path can launch a TRON wildcard pattern search such as:
+
+```text
+TA*CDEFG
+```
+
+That pattern means:
+
+- fixed leading `T`
+- `A` as `prefix_after_t`
+- any middle characters
+- `CDEFG` as suffix 5
+
+This is not a performance benchmark.
+
+## Current Implementation
+
+- `TRON_ADDR` is a separate address type.
+- `T...` wildcard patterns select TRON search.
+- GPU pattern mode calls `ComputeKeysTronPattern`.
+- GPU returns the 20-byte TRON payload body.
+- CPU reconstructs the TRON Base58Check address and verifies the candidate key.
+
+The current TRON GPU pattern path uses full address construction for pattern matching. It is intended as a functional bridge before adding faster prefix/suffix filters.
+
+## RunPod Build And Smoke
+
+On a short-lived CUDA-capable RunPod Pod, after applying the candidate patch:
+
+```bash
+ALLOW_RUNPOD_TRON_GPU_PATTERN_SMOKE=1 CUDA_ARCH=80 scripts/runpod_tron_gpu_pattern_search_smoke.sh
+```
+
+`timeout` exit code `124` is acceptable for this smoke if there is no crash before timeout.
+
+The default smoke pattern is intentionally longer than the product's 5-character suffix so an accidental hit is very unlikely during a short compile/run check. Product-rule matching is covered by `scripts/runpod_verify_tron_gpu_address_layer.sh`.
+
+## Safety
+
+- Do not run this on `47.80.70.211`.
+- Do not treat this as a speed result.
+- Do not use customer patterns or customer data.
+- Do not rely on plaintext output for production.
+- Production return must still be handled by the Python wrapper and age encryption.
+
+## Next Gate
+
+After this smoke compiles and runs on RunPod, add optimized GPU prefix-after-T and suffix filters so the hot path does not Base58-encode every candidate unless needed.
diff --git a/scripts/runpod_tron_gpu_pattern_search_smoke.sh b/scripts/runpod_tron_gpu_pattern_search_smoke.sh
new file mode 100755
index 0000000..c7e9640
--- /dev/null
+++ b/scripts/runpod_tron_gpu_pattern_search_smoke.sh
@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@
+#!/usr/bin/env bash
+set -euo pipefail
+
+if [ "${ALLOW_RUNPOD_TRON_GPU_PATTERN_SMOKE:-0}" != "1" ]; then
+  echo "refusing_to_run_without_ALLOW_RUNPOD_TRON_GPU_PATTERN_SMOKE=1" >&2
+  echo "This smoke is intended for a short-lived CUDA RunPod Pod only." >&2
+  exit 2
+fi
+
+CUDA_HOME="${CUDA_HOME:-/usr/local/cuda}"
+CUDA_ARCH="${CUDA_ARCH:-80}"
+CXXCUDA="${CXXCUDA:-/usr/bin/g++}"
+SMOKE_PATTERN="${SMOKE_PATTERN:-TA*123456789ABCDEFGH}"
+SMOKE_SECONDS="${SMOKE_SECONDS:-10}"
+
+echo "== build VanitySearch with GPU support"
+make gpu=1 CCAP="$CUDA_ARCH" CUDA="$CUDA_HOME" CXXCUDA="$CXXCUDA" all
+
+echo "== run bounded TRON GPU pattern smoke"
+set +e
+timeout "$SMOKE_SECONDS"s ./VanitySearch -gpu -t 0 -g 8,128 "$SMOKE_PATTERN" \
+  > /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stdout.txt \
+  2> /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stderr.txt
+rc=$?
+set -e
+
+if [ "$rc" -ne 0 ] && [ "$rc" -ne 124 ]; then
+  echo "tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_failed rc=$rc" >&2
+  tail -80 /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stdout.txt >&2 || true
+  tail -80 /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stderr.txt >&2 || true
+  exit 1
+fi
+
+if grep -Eiq "Priv|WIF|HEX|private_key|mnemonic|seed|token|secret" \
+  /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stdout.txt /tmp/tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_stderr.txt; then
+  echo "unexpected sensitive marker or hit output in TRON GPU pattern smoke" >&2
+  exit 1
+fi
+
+echo "tron_gpu_pattern_smoke_passed"
-- 
